{
  "texts": [
    "To overcome these security limitations and ensure the secure delivery of software products while preserving DevOps agility, the concept of DevSecOps (Development, Security, and Operations) emerged.",
    "DevSecOps involves considering application and infrastructure security from the outset and automating certain security gates to prevent slowdowns in the DevOps workflow [265].",
    "However, incorporating security practices into DevOps to achieve DevSecOps poses several challenges.",
    "Common security practices, such as security code review [89], often demand significant manual effort, potentially hindering the agility of DevOps.",
    "While automated tools like static application security testing (SAST) can assist in identifying vulnerabilities during code review, they still face limitations in practical effectiveness, especially in real-world scenarios [26]."
  ]
}